div.p:
               YOur former Letter gave me an Account of Your
own and others Dissatisfaction about the Oaths;
but your second carries the Point a great deal farther;
for therein you tell me, Those who are unsatisfied,
think themselves bound to separate from the Communion
of those who have taken them; and that if Ease be not given
to the Scrupulous, new Congregations will be immediately formed;
and therefore you beg my Assistance in clearing these
Points, in order to the preventing a New Separation.
